10/12/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A senior official with the Ministry of Economy and Energy was arrested on Friday (December 8th) for suspected abuse of office related to classified information, prosecutors announced. Pavel Pavlov, a head of the ministry's Information and Communication Security office, is accused of using secret information supplied by the Interior Ministry, the Defence Ministry and intelligence agency, to benefit illegally and support money-laundering activities. Other two people -- Pavlov's colleague, Tanya Tancheva, and a businessman, Rumen Obreshkov, also were detained. (bTV, Darik - 08/12/06) 
